1
00:01:27,370 --> 00:01:31,900
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,130 --> 00:01:34,940
[Episode 4]

3
00:01:47,620 --> 00:01:50,160
[Lihai Toll Station]

4
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:53,400
Mom,

5
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,430
do hamsters get carsick?

6
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:00,000
Do we have to bring it?

7
00:02:00,710 --> 00:02:01,560
How about

8
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,600
we ask Aunt Feng
to take care of it for a few days?

9
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,590
You forgot—

10
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:07,800
Aunt Feng is terrified of rodents.

11
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:10,190
I'll talk to Grandma.

12
00:02:10,190 --> 00:02:11,120
It's very clean.

13
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:12,350
It's not dirty at all.

14
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,590
Hello, Dr. Luo.

15
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:35,670
I'm sorry, Ms. Yan.

16
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,810
You sent me so many messages,

17
00:02:37,810 --> 00:02:39,070
and I just saw them now.

18
00:02:40,079 --> 00:02:41,360
I only sent two.

19
00:02:41,790 --> 00:02:43,310
I've been on a business trip
these past few days

20
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:45,380
and didn't have time to check my phone.

21
00:02:45,380 --> 00:02:47,220
Do you need any help?

22
00:02:49,650 --> 00:02:50,630
The thing is...

23
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:59,450
I want to take Jiale back
to my hometown for a few days.

24
00:03:00,690 --> 00:03:02,020
I took your advice

25
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,460
and want him

26
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,060
to say a proper goodbye to his Godmother.

27
00:03:06,590 --> 00:03:08,700
And this hamster...

28
00:03:10,610 --> 00:03:12,610
It's inconvenient to bring, right?

29
00:03:13,330 --> 00:03:14,450
I'm really sorry.

30
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:17,370
I originally wanted
to help ease Jiale's mood.

31
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,930
I didn't expect it
to become a trouble for you.

32
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:20,820
How about this?

33
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:22,840
You leave more food for it.

34
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:24,620
It'll be fine for two or three days.

35
00:03:24,620 --> 00:03:26,870
My work in Gangdao isn't finished yet,

36
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:28,940
so I can't rush back today.

37
00:03:29,590 --> 00:03:30,600
Forget it.

38
00:03:31,079 --> 00:03:32,280
We'll bring it along.

39
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:34,930
Leaving the hamster alone at home—

40
00:03:35,230 --> 00:03:36,550
we won't be at ease

41
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,480
if it runs out of food and water.

42
00:03:38,570 --> 00:03:40,110
I really made it hard for you.

43
00:03:40,110 --> 00:03:41,170
When you come back,

44
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:43,240
you must give me a chance

45
00:03:43,310 --> 00:03:44,870
to treat you to a nice meal.

46
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,079
No need.

47
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:47,000
You must.

48
00:03:47,510 --> 00:03:48,170
Promise me.

49
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,720
I also want to thank Jiale in person.

50
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:51,470
Okay.

51
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:52,990
Great.

52
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,280
It's a deal.

53
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:56,150
Drive carefully.

54
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,060
Call me as soon as you get back.

55
00:03:58,160 --> 00:03:58,900
You promise.

56
00:04:00,260 --> 00:04:01,340
I gotta go.

57
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,100
I still have patients.

58
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,400
See you when you get back.

59
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,750
Okay. Bye.

60
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,980
Keep your eyes on the road.

61
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:32,270
I was wrong. I was wrong.

62
00:04:32,270 --> 00:04:33,190
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

63
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:35,390
I beg you. I beg you.

64
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:37,620
Please.

65
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,880
Raise your head a little.

66
00:04:47,850 --> 00:04:49,409
So, what exactly happened?

67
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:53,830
He was drunk.

68
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:56,040
After he got home,

69
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,530
he went straight

70
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,930
to bed.

71
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:01,870
I got him a glass of water.

72
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,240
And then?

73
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,430
And then... And then...

74
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:06,310
I... I...

75
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,350
I hit her.

76
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:12,160
Then he suddenly got up,

77
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:15,680
grabbed me by the neck,

78
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:17,310
and started beating me.

79
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:20,310
Why are you beating me?

80
00:05:20,310 --> 00:05:21,330
Why?

81
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:24,510
Do I need a reason?

82
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,790
I can beat you if I'm unhappy!

83
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:30,360
Run?

84
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:34,520
No.

85
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:36,750
I'm sorry. I was wrong.

86
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,200
You think that's enough?

87
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,070
I put a roof over your head,

88
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:42,390
and you despise me?

89
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:44,120
I don't know why.

90
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,870
I really don't know why.

91
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:51,870
I... I really can't remember.

92
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,680
After I went back,

93
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,610
she seemed to...

94
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:58,040
she seemed to keep asking me.

95
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:58,920
She asked me

96
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:01,490
if I had another woman on the side.

97
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,720
So you hit her?

98
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:31,560
So I...

99
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,920
I'm a bastard.

100
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:35,430
I'm a bastard.

101
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:37,659
I... I'm sorry to her.

102
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:39,159
-She's such a good woman.
-I failed her.

103
00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:40,560
But you beat her like this.

104
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,950
Hearing you might be detained,

105
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:43,350
she even pleaded for you.

106
00:06:44,390 --> 00:06:45,920
She really wants to settle?

107
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,090
After all this,

108
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:50,010
are you sure you still want
to settle with him?

109
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,600
Will Godfather come?

110
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,240
Probably not.

111
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:09,520
He seems pretty busy.

112
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:13,240
Is Godfather too sad?

113
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:15,640
After Godmother passed away,

114
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:17,950
he doesn't even play games anymore.

115
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,810
If Godmother can't see him,

116
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,680
will she be sad?

117
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,130
Let's go.

118
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,210
Let's go.

119
00:07:36,070 --> 00:07:36,870
Grandma Jian.

120
00:07:37,610 --> 00:07:39,520
Why did you move here?

121
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:41,080
It's too run-down here.

122
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:42,040
Jiale,

123
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:43,850
don't talk nonsense.

124
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:45,520
We sold the old house.

125
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:48,980
Now it's just me and Grandma Jian.

126
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,159
This room is enough for us.

127
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:54,070
Uncle,

128
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:57,240
I want to talk to you
about Leilei's house.

129
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,550
Before,

130
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,300
she mortgaged the house.

131
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:06,560
Now they are coming to take it away.

132
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,870
I should have known it.

133
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:12,460
This child...

134
00:08:12,870 --> 00:08:14,040
I know her too well.

135
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,800
If she weren't driven to a corner

136
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,210
and had no other choice,

137
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,970
she wouldn't have touched
other people's money.

138
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:33,650
[Officer Li]

139
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:34,210
[Is he Xia Yi?]

140
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:38,620
Yes.

141
00:08:38,809 --> 00:08:40,250
It's Xu's photo.

142
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:41,600
Before this,

143
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,750
didn't you police officers
come to investigate?

144
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:44,550
The person you are looking for

145
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:45,360
is not him.

146
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:47,270
Other police officers have looked for him?

147
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:47,850
Yes.

148
00:08:47,910 --> 00:08:49,040
Not only the police,

149
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,380
but also two or three groups
of young girls.

150
00:08:49,710 --> 00:08:50,420
[Is he Xia Yi?]

151
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:54,520
[He isn't Xia Yi.]

152
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:53,790
They said Xu was in online relationships
with them,

153
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:54,750
asked them to invest,

154
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:56,790
and swindled them out of a lot of money.

155
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:57,630
Mr. Xing,

156
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,780
do you have a group photo

157
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:01,600
of all your rescue team members?

158
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:02,390
Yes.

159
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:06,790
Xu

160
00:09:06,790 --> 00:09:08,370
is a good guy in our team.

161
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:10,810
A while ago, during a mission,

162
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,360
he was injured while saving someone.

163
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,390
He's been in the hospital,

164
00:09:13,390 --> 00:09:14,450
in a coma.

165
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:15,870
It was just last week

166
00:09:15,870 --> 00:09:17,530
that his hand could move a bit.

167
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,150
When they checked the timeline,
it didn't match at all—

168
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:20,550
They found it was not him.

169
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,750
Everyone is here.

170
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:23,150
Okay.

171
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,950
Which bastard

172
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,130
used Xu's photo to scam people?

173
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,600
That's just disgusting.

174
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:34,670
Is there one person named Xia Yi?

175
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:37,200
There's no one
with the last name Xia on our team.

176
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,150
A woman also called to ask about him.

177
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:40,360
When we're busy,

178
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,600
we have some temporary volunteers
to help out.

179
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,840
But there were too many people,

180
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:45,170
so I couldn't remember.

181
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:48,270
Okay.

182
00:09:48,970 --> 00:09:49,590
Thank you.

183
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:50,600
Thank you.

184
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:53,100
[Officer Li]

185
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:51,230
Take care.

186
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:52,480
Then,

187
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,980
let's leave a contact method.

188
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:55,320
[Xia Yi is not in this photo.]

189
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:56,000
If there are any important clues,

190
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,400
contact me immediately.

191
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:57,840
Okay.

192
00:09:57,870 --> 00:09:58,240
Okay.

193
00:09:58,240 --> 00:09:58,570
Okay.

194
00:09:58,820 --> 00:09:59,080
Here.

195
00:09:59,080 --> 00:09:59,410
Here.

196
00:10:00,930 --> 00:10:02,010
This is my number. Take it down.

197
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:01,940
[Xia Yi is not in this photo.]

198
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:04,980
[Thank you for your investigation.
Thank you.]

199
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:02,360
Okay.

200
00:10:02,820 --> 00:10:03,670
I will just take it down.

201
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:04,000
Here.

202
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:06,890
[I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have said that to you.]

203
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:33,530
Godmother.

204
00:10:33,770 --> 00:10:34,910
I miss you so much.

205
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:38,710
Whenever I think
of not being able to see you again,

206
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:40,800
I get so scared.

207
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:43,500
I really want to see you,

208
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,980
but I can't even dream about you.

209
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,010
I dreamed about her.

210
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:52,720
Xia.

211
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,120
You are here.

212
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:54,960
Xia is here.

213
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:55,550
Uncle. Auntie.

214
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:56,210
Godfather.

215
00:10:58,390 --> 00:10:59,450
It has been 35 days.

216
00:11:00,150 --> 00:11:01,270
I believe Leilei

217
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,420
will come back to visit us.

218
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,360
Leilei.

219
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,480
It was my fault

220
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,690
for not taking good care of you.

221
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:25,000
We agreed

222
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:27,440
to use your favorite

223
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:29,570
tulips for the bouquet at our wedding.

224
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:32,620
But too bad I don't have
that kind of luck.

225
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:45,120
Jiale,

226
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,200
you've grown taller.

227
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,240
Later,

228
00:11:51,030 --> 00:11:53,360
I need to pay the cemetery management fee.

229
00:11:53,470 --> 00:11:54,470
You come with me.

230
00:11:58,630 --> 00:11:59,760
Who are you, really?

231
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,120
What did you do to Leilei?

232
00:12:05,490 --> 00:12:06,420
I've told Leilei

233
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:08,360
about this before.

234
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:11,770
Actually, my name is not Xia Yi.

235
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:14,630
I'm an overseas Pazion Chinese.

236
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:17,060
My family is in the gem business.

237
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:21,630
Over the past couple of years, they've been
gradually handing the business over to me

238
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:23,960
and sent me here
to explore the Chinese market.

239
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,690
To make doing business easier,

240
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:28,060
I gave myself a Chinese name—

241
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:29,270
Xia Yi.

242
00:12:29,940 --> 00:12:31,640
Then, when something happened to Leilei,

243
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,620
why didn't you go to the police?

244
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:35,630
You know,

245
00:12:35,980 --> 00:12:37,790
a gemstone can be worth ten thousand,

246
00:12:37,790 --> 00:12:39,390
a hundred thousand, or even more.

247
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:40,440
There's even jade gambling.

248
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:43,170
There's a lot of room
to operate in this business.

249
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:46,000
With our family business running
for so many years,

250
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,060
there are bound to be some gray areas.

251
00:12:49,390 --> 00:12:50,750
So over the past years,

252
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:52,600
I've tried my best to avoid

253
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,000
dealing with the police.

254
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:56,200
So you lied to the police

255
00:12:56,390 --> 00:12:58,120
and told them you were doing rescue work?

256
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,580
It was all fake, wasn't it?

257
00:12:59,890 --> 00:13:01,150
Not entirely.

258
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:04,390
I know my business isn't honorable,

259
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:06,520
so I always wanted to do some good deeds

260
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,720
to atone for my sins.

261
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:11,240
But to join a formal rescue team,

262
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:13,840
I have to register
with the Civil Affairs Bureau.

263
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,640
I had no choice

264
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:17,100
but to just help out

265
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,210
and volunteer.

266
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,600
Leilei knew about this, too.

267
00:13:21,630 --> 00:13:22,840
Then did Leilei know

268
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,360
that the watches

269
00:13:25,510 --> 00:13:25,870
and bags you gave her

270
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:26,870
were all fake?

271
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,750
I had the things you gave her

272
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,010
appraised.

273
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,440
Not a single one is real.

274
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,600
Not even one.

275
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,720
How could they be fake?

276
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:37,240
I picked them out
with Leilei at the boutiques.

277
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:39,040
We have receipts for all of them.

278
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:42,200
I'll show you the transaction records,

279
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:42,720
okay?

280
00:13:46,290 --> 00:13:47,070
Never mind.

281
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,410
Look at this one.

282
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:51,450
How does it look?

283
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:54,200
Do you really think it looks good?

284
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,110
Yes, it does.

285
00:13:55,150 --> 00:13:56,440
But isn't it a bit expensive?

286
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,150
And

287
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:59,360
aren't the diamonds a bit too much?

288
00:13:59,390 --> 00:14:00,720
It has to be over the top.

289
00:14:00,790 --> 00:14:03,080
My girl deserves
something sparkly like this

290
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:05,430
to outshine those rich clients of yours.

291
00:14:06,030 --> 00:14:06,870
Stop it.

292
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:08,410
Check, please.

293
00:14:10,270 --> 00:14:11,090
Leilei

294
00:14:12,260 --> 00:14:13,920
must have been short on money,

295
00:14:14,510 --> 00:14:16,260
so she sold the real ones,

296
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:17,950
swapped them with fakes,

297
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:21,160
and made sure I wouldn't find out.

298
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,840
Why would she do that?

299
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:28,570
There's something

300
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:30,980
I've never told anyone.

301
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:33,320
I once accidentally

302
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,630
found that kind of photo

303
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:38,550
in Leilei's phone.

304
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:40,960
What kind of photo?

305
00:14:42,890 --> 00:14:44,410
Nude photos taken

306
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,330
while holding her ID.

307
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:47,280
[Name: Jian Leilei]

308
00:14:51,130 --> 00:14:51,930
Are you saying

309
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,240
that Leilei

310
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,800
got involved in one of
those nude loan schemes?

311
00:14:58,150 --> 00:14:59,420
So I guess

312
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:01,660
Leilei's tattoo

313
00:15:02,550 --> 00:15:04,120
was also done

314
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,120
at their request.

315
00:15:07,910 --> 00:15:09,040
That's impossible.

316
00:15:20,030 --> 00:15:20,580
This

317
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:24,010
is the avatar you used in the game.

318
00:15:24,510 --> 00:15:26,200
Leilei had an octopus tattoo.

319
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:29,960
If her tattoo had nothing to do with you,

320
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:31,840
why did you

321
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,080
use an octopus as your avatar?

322
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:35,530
Why?

323
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,000
Because I love Leilei.

324
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:39,630
Since I love her,

325
00:15:39,630 --> 00:15:40,750
I must love everything about her,

326
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,750
including her flaws.

327
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:45,360
I changed my avatar to this

328
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:47,080
just to let her know

329
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,720
that I don't mind her past.

330
00:15:56,910 --> 00:15:57,970
That can't be real.

331
00:15:58,640 --> 00:16:00,100
If that's really the case,

332
00:16:02,010 --> 00:16:04,040
how could I not feel anything?

333
00:16:05,330 --> 00:16:06,960
How could I not know anything?

334
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:09,360
That's because
she didn't want you to know.

335
00:16:10,180 --> 00:16:11,540
In her heart,

336
00:16:11,910 --> 00:16:14,030
you and Jiale were much more
important than me.

337
00:16:14,030 --> 00:16:14,960
In her suicide note,

338
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,560
she didn't mention me at all.

339
00:16:17,730 --> 00:16:19,180
She only mentioned you,

340
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:21,270
didn't she?

341
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:35,780
You can go verify it.

342
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:37,930
[Name: Pongsri Leekpa]

343
00:16:36,150 --> 00:16:38,030
The worst that can happen
is my family's business gets exposed.

344
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:39,790
I'll just be deported

345
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:42,050
and never be able to come back.

346
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:45,360
I will.

347
00:16:47,370 --> 00:16:48,310
[Name: Pongsri Leekpa]

348
00:16:49,670 --> 00:16:50,470
[Name: Pongsri Leekpa]

349
00:17:02,430 --> 00:17:05,250
Every time Godmother
peels an apple for me,

350
00:17:05,589 --> 00:17:06,589
she'd cut it

351
00:17:06,589 --> 00:17:08,319
into little bunny shapes, too.

352
00:17:09,030 --> 00:17:10,310
Then have some more.

353
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:14,970
Coming.

354
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:22,310
Are the cemetery matters

355
00:17:22,310 --> 00:17:23,140
taken care of?

356
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,700
Yes. Don't worry.

357
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:26,339
Come sit for a while.

358
00:17:26,339 --> 00:17:27,170
I won't sit.

359
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,590
We have to go to my mom's.

360
00:17:37,540 --> 00:17:38,000
Jiale,

361
00:17:38,420 --> 00:17:39,040
let's go.

362
00:17:46,850 --> 00:17:47,730
Grandpa Jian,

363
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,240
can you help me take care
of the hamster tonight?

364
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,160
No problem.

365
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:54,330
I'll take it tomorrow.

366
00:17:54,730 --> 00:17:56,270
Don't bother Grandpa Jian.

367
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:57,960
Don't be silly.

368
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,020
Just leave it here.

369
00:17:59,310 --> 00:18:00,920
Your mom is a clean freak.

370
00:18:02,510 --> 00:18:04,870
When Leilei was little, she had a kitten.

371
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,550
She wanted to give you one of its babies,

372
00:18:06,550 --> 00:18:08,210
but you didn't dare to take it.

373
00:18:12,130 --> 00:18:13,360
I mean,

374
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:15,830
when you come to pick up
the hamster tomorrow,

375
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:17,650
I can see Jiale again,

376
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:18,270
right?

377
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:19,790
Good boy.

378
00:18:20,340 --> 00:18:21,070
Good boy.

379
00:18:23,190 --> 00:18:24,560
Say hi to your mom for me.

380
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:26,760
We'll get going.

381
00:18:27,270 --> 00:18:28,110
Go on.

382
00:18:29,110 --> 00:18:31,110
Bye-bye, Grandpa and Grandma Jian.

383
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:35,040
Take care.

384
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:03,000
Why were you so mean to Godfather today?

385
00:19:04,070 --> 00:19:04,920
Godmother is gone.

386
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,720
He's had it hard enough already.

387
00:19:09,610 --> 00:19:11,340
You really like him, don't you?

388
00:19:11,790 --> 00:19:12,680
Of course.

389
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:14,760
He's not just nice to me.

390
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:16,930
He treats Godmother even better.

391
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,350
Every time Godmother was with him,

392
00:19:19,380 --> 00:19:20,740
she laughed so happily.

393
00:19:37,310 --> 00:19:37,880
Can you handle them?

394
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:38,400
Yes.

395
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,170
Let's go.

396
00:19:42,010 --> 00:19:45,840
[No Soliciting]

397
00:19:44,790 --> 00:19:45,480
Be good

398
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:46,400
at Grandma's.

399
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:47,350
Got it?

400
00:19:52,030 --> 00:19:52,480
Mom.

401
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:53,930
Grandma.

402
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:55,690
Jiale, come in.

403
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:56,340
Come in.

404
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,220
Here.

405
00:19:59,350 --> 00:20:00,410
Change your shoes.

406
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:03,520
Don't forget to wash your hands.

407
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:10,580
You go in first.

408
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:18,810
Good boy, Jiale.

409
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,790
Do it with your mom.

410
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:21,390
Come here.

411
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:26,890
Dad.

412
00:20:27,070 --> 00:20:28,390
We're here to see Mom.

413
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:29,810
Jiale is back, too.

414
00:20:32,550 --> 00:20:33,270
Grandpa.

415
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,310
Mom told me

416
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:36,960
she missed you a lot.

417
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:38,470
How dare she say that?

418
00:20:39,350 --> 00:20:41,200
She came back and didn't
even visit her family first,

419
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,900
but ran off to show filial piety
at someone else's house.

420
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:44,980
But today is my Godmother's death anniversary.

421
00:20:44,980 --> 00:20:46,240
-No buts.
-Godmother—

422
00:20:47,070 --> 00:20:48,800
Burn the incense before we eat.

423
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,720
Come on, Jiale. Time for bed.

424
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:01,960
Wait a minute.

425
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,200
I need to sort out

426
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:04,590
Godmother's photos on my pad

427
00:21:04,590 --> 00:21:06,450
and forward them to Grandpa Jian.

428
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:07,480
You still have to sleep.

429
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:08,590
Look what time it is.

430
00:21:08,590 --> 00:21:09,590
Wait a minute!

431
00:21:09,590 --> 00:21:10,320
Be a good boy.

432
00:21:10,750 --> 00:21:11,110
Wait.

433
00:21:21,110 --> 00:21:21,920
You

434
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:23,740
don't spoil Jiale too much.

435
00:21:25,510 --> 00:21:27,710
Leilei's matter has a big impact on him.

436
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:29,960
And he means well.

437
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,810
I shouldn't speak ill of the dead.

438
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:35,640
But,

439
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,110
you young people

440
00:21:37,510 --> 00:21:39,100
are just too selfish,

441
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:41,890
making the old bury the young.

442
00:21:42,030 --> 00:21:43,400
How could

443
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:44,860
she do such a thing?

444
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:47,400
What's worth committing suicide for?

445
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:49,690
She was too fragile.

446
00:21:53,590 --> 00:21:54,280
Mom.

447
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:56,730
I bought you a foot basin.

448
00:21:57,030 --> 00:21:58,200
Soak your feet in your free time.

449
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,660
It's good for your health.

450
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,580
I don't want it.

451
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:02,320
You're wasting money again.

452
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:05,880
Don't touch them.

453
00:22:07,510 --> 00:22:08,770
These are for your dad.

454
00:22:13,990 --> 00:22:15,310
After you go back to Lihai,

455
00:22:15,310 --> 00:22:16,970
go see Uncle Ding.

456
00:22:17,190 --> 00:22:18,430
He's not doing well.

457
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,240
Why is he back?

458
00:22:24,790 --> 00:22:26,320
They say that he got cancer.

459
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:28,530
He couldn't be cured abroad.

460
00:22:28,530 --> 00:22:29,860
So he wanted to come back

461
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:31,220
and return to his roots.

462
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:36,000
I've been quite busy with school lately.

463
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:36,920
I might not

464
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:38,200
have the time.

465
00:22:40,110 --> 00:22:41,520
Why are you so selfish?

466
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:45,000
You only care about your own business.

467
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,070
Do you know how much

468
00:22:46,070 --> 00:22:47,270
he helped our family?

469
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,920
Our school was shut down and merged.

470
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,030
If Uncle Ding hadn't

471
00:22:51,030 --> 00:22:52,160
stepped in to help,

472
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:54,420
do you know how much less pension I'd get,

473
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:58,120
and how much less medical insurance
would cover if I got sick?

474
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:01,590
Mom,

475
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:04,240
if you don't have enough money,

476
00:23:04,310 --> 00:23:05,590
you can just tell me.

477
00:23:06,030 --> 00:23:07,380
Is it about money?

478
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:08,720
In your heart,

479
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,650
this family simply doesn't exist.

480
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:14,030
Uncle Ding was just

481
00:23:14,310 --> 00:23:15,960
your dad's little underling back then,

482
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:18,030
but he values relationships
much more than you do.

483
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:20,400
He sends things every holiday.

484
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:24,960
The same goes for this time.

485
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:26,070
I didn't ask him.

486
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,030
He heard about it himself

487
00:23:28,030 --> 00:23:29,160
and offered to help.

488
00:23:30,270 --> 00:23:31,010
But,

489
00:23:31,550 --> 00:23:33,310
you're quite unhappy.

490
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:34,810
Baffling.

491
00:23:37,070 --> 00:23:38,600
Just go when you are told to.

492
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:41,490
Don't be as ignorant
as when you were a kid.

493
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,060
Does it sound good?

494
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,110
Yes.

495
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,610
Thank you, Dad.

496
00:25:43,670 --> 00:25:44,300
Master,

497
00:25:44,580 --> 00:25:45,700
you heard it too.

498
00:25:45,820 --> 00:25:47,070
First, the poisoned crabs,

499
00:25:47,070 --> 00:25:48,240
then the rescue team.

500
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:50,370
How could there be such a coincidence?

501
00:25:50,510 --> 00:25:52,110
Let me investigate further.

502
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,270
Issue me a letter of introduction

503
00:25:53,270 --> 00:25:55,720
and let me verify it
with the Immigration Office.

504
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:56,640
I'm begging you.

505
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:58,200
Regarding the telecom fraud,

506
00:25:58,200 --> 00:26:00,480
I have already contacted
our CID colleagues.

507
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:01,510
It's different.

508
00:26:01,590 --> 00:26:03,790
These people never showed their faces.

509
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:05,270
They just grabbed a random photo online

510
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:07,070
and used it as a profile picture.

511
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:08,750
Xia Yi

512
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:10,350
is a living person.

513
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:12,440
That's a great lead.

514
00:26:12,550 --> 00:26:13,160
Isn't it?

515
00:26:14,070 --> 00:26:15,960
Have you finished your own work?

516
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:16,440
I have.

517
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:17,540
The report,

518
00:26:17,830 --> 00:26:19,030
the monthly summary,

519
00:26:19,030 --> 00:26:21,560
and the 5,000-word work report
you asked for—

520
00:26:22,030 --> 00:26:22,720
I wrote them all.

521
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:24,350
Not a single punctuation mark is missing.

522
00:26:24,350 --> 00:26:26,750
What about the correspondent copy
for Lihai Daily?

523
00:26:26,750 --> 00:26:29,150
The correspondent copy for Lihai Daily...

524
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:46,680
Mr. Li.

525
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:48,750
Chief Hu wants you
to run an errand for him.

526
00:26:48,750 --> 00:26:49,920
He said there is a foreigner
in our jurisdiction

527
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:51,070
whose visa has expired or something.

528
00:26:51,070 --> 00:26:51,870
He wants you to go

529
00:26:51,870 --> 00:26:54,200
to the Immigration Office to ask about it.

530
00:26:54,350 --> 00:26:55,950
You can just call...

531
00:26:56,350 --> 00:26:57,750
Just make a phone call...

532
00:27:04,510 --> 00:27:06,240
I've already prepared
the letter of introduction for you.

533
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:07,790
Don't delay your own work.

534
00:27:09,410 --> 00:27:12,330
[Mingde International Hospital,
Lihai City]

535
00:27:14,830 --> 00:27:17,580
[VVIP suite] [Ding Zhibo]

536
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:22,880
You must be Yan Ling.

537
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:32,010
Have a seat. Have a seat.

538
00:27:33,830 --> 00:27:35,190
About my mom's retirement,

539
00:27:35,190 --> 00:27:35,940
thank you.

540
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,750
She's had it tough on her own.

541
00:27:38,750 --> 00:27:40,080
Since you were too busy,

542
00:27:40,110 --> 00:27:42,270
I had to lend a hand. Take a seat.

543
00:27:46,590 --> 00:27:47,440
Over the years,

544
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:48,160
I've treated

545
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:50,160
your family's affairs as my own.

546
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:51,140
You know that.

547
00:27:52,750 --> 00:27:53,420
Thank you.

548
00:27:55,070 --> 00:27:56,800
I'm not looking for a thank you.

549
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,210
It's been so many years,

550
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:00,680
and I haven't heard from you at all.

551
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:02,410
You even avoided me on purpose.

552
00:28:02,550 --> 00:28:04,010
It really breaks my heart.

553
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:09,760
Your mom told me everything.

554
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:12,160
You've made great progress lately.

555
00:28:13,030 --> 00:28:14,030
That's very good.

556
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:15,750
If your dad knew,

557
00:28:16,230 --> 00:28:18,360
he would definitely be very relieved.

558
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:21,720
Indeed.

559
00:28:23,930 --> 00:28:25,230
Back then,

560
00:28:26,070 --> 00:28:27,470
we both had our problems.

561
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:30,160
We should find a chance to clear the air.

562
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:31,160
What do you think?

563
00:28:32,150 --> 00:28:32,880
Also...

564
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:36,440
I'm divorced now.

565
00:28:39,750 --> 00:28:40,830
The dosage, I think...

566
00:28:40,830 --> 00:28:42,480
As long as his mental state is stable,

567
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:43,340
that's enough.

568
00:28:43,550 --> 00:28:44,270
Okay, Dr. Luo.

569
00:28:44,270 --> 00:28:45,720
We'll talk about it later.

570
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:47,320
No problem. Call me anytime.

571
00:28:47,350 --> 00:28:47,790
Okay.

572
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:49,480
Looking forward to working together more.

573
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:50,050
Alright, see you.

574
00:28:50,050 --> 00:28:51,250
See you, Director He.

575
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:55,540
Ms. Yan?

576
00:28:58,550 --> 00:28:59,640
What a coincidence.

